Green Light Australia are looking for a Red Hat Linux Expert to assist in
delivering projects for a leading Industry provider. The Linux expert will be
supporting a large NFVI cloud. In this role the Red Hat Linux will work
closely with customers to solve problems and establish working relationships
with them. You will collaborate with their sales and technical delivery teams
to help them find the best solutions from across the Red Hat Enterprise Linux
(RHEL) portfolio and other associated offerings.  
  
The Red Hat Linux Expert will need excellent communication and interpersonal
skills to be able to maintain high-quality customer experience with Red Hat
and have technical expertise, passion for open source and a thorough
understanding of business processes.  
  
** Responsibilities: **

  * Support the delivery team with recommendations for development and implementation of complex solutions. 
  * Deployment and service objectives, while sustaining good relationships with current and prospective customers. 
  * Build solutions based on customer requirements and create and deliver solid business cases. 
  * Design architectures focused on value and present the application and return on investment of those technologies. 
  * Use your skills and knowledge to ensure customer satisfaction. 
  * Share knowledge to allow team members to learn from your successes and mistakes. 
  
** Requirements ** ** : **

  * Experience as an Engineer, consultant or an equivalent role with enterprise environments. 
  * Linux systems, preferably in Red Hat platform solutions like Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL), Red Hat Network Satellite or Red Hat Virtualization. 
  * Experience with Red Hat Enterprise Linux STIG, with the ability to implement recommendations. 
  * Advanced knowledge of open-source cloud Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) solutions like Red Hat OpenStack Platform, KVM, VMware, etc. 
  * Knowledge of compliance and hardening tools like Open SCAP (and its related standards like CVE, OVAL, XCCDF), Atomic Scan, SSG, and CIS Benchmarks. 
  * Knowledge of technologies like clustering, directory services, identity management, etc. 
  * Experience working with system integrators. 
  * Ability to interpret customers' business and technical needs. 
  * Understanding of complex enterprise solutions and architectures. 
  * Record of developing relationships at engineering, commercial, and executive levels throughout large enterprise IT organizations. 
  
** Nice to Have: **

  * Experience with programming languages like Python, Perl, Ruby, or shell scripting. 
  * Cybersecurity certification like OSCP, CEH, CISSP, or OSCE. 
  
Green Light is one of the most successful and fastest growing IT services
businesses. We offer a wide range of IT services in Security, infrastructure
and Systems Integration to a diverse customer base throughout Australia, New
Zealand, SE Asia and Europe.

